{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/hello-world/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Khizar's Blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"d6251585-78a0-55d8-8d47-fd5529c73d40","excerpt":"Wow, this shit is working finally. I'm inside a  file and writing markdown stuff. Wait let me just make things a bit easier for me - let's add visual Studioâ€¦","html":"<p>Wow, this shit is working finally. I'm inside a <code class=\"language-text\">.md</code> file and writing markdown stuff. Wait let me just make things a bit easier for me - let's add visual Studio Code extensions. This will make sure that my blogging journey is a lot smoother. Weeelll, I think we need:</p>\n<h5><strong>1. Auto correction</strong></h5>\n<p>I make typos quite a lot. Let's try to minimize that in my upcomming blogs. For that, I will be adding the <a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=streetsidesoftware.code-spell-checker\">Code Spell Checker</a>. It took me 2-seconds to install, and I'm already seeing in my <code class=\"language-text\">.md</code> file, perfect.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/70e722eeabc5882f2a2a395a4a5622b2/51800/showingTypos.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 25.316455696202528%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"A picture of the typos in my md file.\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/70e722eeabc5882f2a2a395a4a5622b2/f058b/showingTypos.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/70e722eeabc5882f2a2a395a4a5622b2/c26ae/showingTypos.png 158w,\n/static/70e722eeabc5882f2a2a395a4a5622b2/6bdcf/showingTypos.png 315w,\n/static/70e722eeabc5882f2a2a395a4a5622b2/f058b/showingTypos.png 630w,\n/static/70e722eeabc5882f2a2a395a4a5622b2/40601/showingTypos.png 945w,\n/static/70e722eeabc5882f2a2a395a4a5622b2/51800/showingTypos.png 1196w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span><em>The typos can be seen in the picture above - the extension is working.</em></p>\n<h5><strong>2. A viewer for my <code class=\"language-text\">.md</code> files</strong></h5>\n<p>All of my blog posts will be <code class=\"language-text\">.md</code> files, including this post. It would therefore make sense to install a Visual Studio Code extension, which can show me the <code class=\"language-text\">.md</code> file outputs in realtime. I found the <a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=shd101wyy.markdown-preview-enhanced\">Markdown Preview Enhanced</a> extension for this exact purpose.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5ea9f4f43b057d02864f4e8733ec89a7/3d4b6/mdPreview.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 85.44303797468356%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"A picture of the typos in my md file.\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/5ea9f4f43b057d02864f4e8733ec89a7/f058b/mdPreview.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5ea9f4f43b057d02864f4e8733ec89a7/c26ae/mdPreview.png 158w,\n/static/5ea9f4f43b057d02864f4e8733ec89a7/6bdcf/mdPreview.png 315w,\n/static/5ea9f4f43b057d02864f4e8733ec89a7/f058b/mdPreview.png 630w,\n/static/5ea9f4f43b057d02864f4e8733ec89a7/3d4b6/mdPreview.png 712w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span><em>We can now preview our MarkDown files. That's very useful.</em></p>\n<p>I think this is all we need for now.</p>\n<p>Although a few things that would be really cool to add would be stuff like LaTeX support in these <code class=\"language-text\">.md</code> files. That would make writing mathematics so much easier. I look forward to enhancing this blog platform by adding such compatibilities (together with like and comment functionalities and animations).</p>\n<p>This total yapping platform is powered by <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.com/\">Gatsby</a>.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Hello World!","date":"June 08, 2025","description":"The first ever post on this site, damn. But how did I get this up and running? What are my plans with it? What now?"}},"previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/building-own-CI-CD/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Building My Own CI Pipeline"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"d6251585-78a0-55d8-8d47-fd5529c73d40","previousPostId":null,"nextPostId":"ec431c30-2f68-5252-8179-b04a63fefeac"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383"],"slicesMap":{}}